You can save and load the settings of individual tracks in Reaper. This does not save the actual audio on the track, just the track channel parameters.

To save a track (and all its settings) go to '''Actions / Track: Save selected track as track template'''


[[File:Reaper save track template.png]]


A dialog box will appear prompting you to enter a name for the saved track



[[File:Reaper track template save prompt.png]]



To open a track template just right click the track header and choose '''Insert track from template''' and then '''Open template'''.



[[File:Reaper open track template.png]]



